        "body": "<p>You are overriding the wrong method. Get rid of the \"s\" at the end of the method name. You need to override <code>paintComponent(...)<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>But, you also need to override the <code>paintComponent(...)<\/code> method of a <code>JPanel<\/code>, You can't just add the method to your class and expect it to work. This is Java 101.<\/p>\n\n<p>Start with the working examples found in the Swing tutorial on <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/painting/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Custom Painting<\/a> <\/p>\n",
